    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The SPA is organized into four thematic sections instead of linear chapters to enhance user exploration: 1) Overview: Introduces the core thesis. 2) The AGI Challenge: Groups foundational concepts and risks (What is AGI, Quantum, ASI, Existential Risk). 3) Legal Fault Lines: Focuses on how AGI breaks existing law (Personhood, IP, Sentience). 4) Governance Blueprints: Presents the proposed solutions (Precautionary Principle, Moderate Regulation, Supranational Models). This thematic structure allows users to dive into areas of interest (e.g., "the problem" vs. "the solution") non-linearly, making the complex information more digestible and engaging. Navigation is handled via a sticky header, and content is revealed dynamically. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 1) Core Concepts (Inform): Interactive cards with hover effects in Overview. 2) AGI vs. Current AI (Compare): HTML table for direct comparison. 3) Governance Analogies (Compare): Chart.js Radar Chart to compare legal models across multiple criteria. 4) Risk Landscape (Organize): Chart.js Polar Area chart to visualize different risk categories. 5) Legal Fault Lines (Organize/Inform): Custom HTML/CSS diagram of a "cracked foundation" where clicking a crack reveals details on the specific legal failure point. 6) Regulatory Tools (Organize): Interactive HTML/Tailwind cards. All choices use JS for interactivity and Chart.js for data visualization, avoiding SVG/Mermaid to adhere to constraints, while supporting the thematic application structure. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
